tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased total carbon dioxide, which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensated respiratory alkalosis. Glycemic control (HbA1c and glucose) is at the upper end of normal, indicating a need for continued monitoring. Renal and electrolyte parameters are unremarkable.
